<bioghist encodinganalog="545">
<p>St. Matthew's Episcopal Church was established in 1955 in Sparta, MI., and it served Sparta's Episcopalian community until its closure in 2003.  Before the church's break up, the congregation grew smaller over the years.  With fewer people going, church officials conducted surveys of its congregation and analyzed their operating costs.  The traditional model of "One Priest, One Parish" was no longer financially viable and too expensive to operate.  The church administration started working on an alternative administrative model called Total Ministry.  This model encourages baptized members of the congregation to take an active role in the ministry.  Instead of the congregation gathered around one minister, everyone in the congregation ministers.</p>
</bioghist>

<scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
<p>The St. Matthew's Episcopal Church records include annual reports, bulletins, clergy reports, correspondence, financial records, meeting minutes, newsletters, and various administrative documents. The records have been arranged into the following series: Administrative Activities; Bulletins; Financial; Newsletters; Bishops' Advisory Committee;  Vestry Meetings; and Registers.</p>
</scopecontent>

